closeMethod.invoke(lexerMock);
verify(lexerMock, times(1)).close(); // This line causes the error, so instead do:
verify(lexerMock, times(1)).getClass().getMethod("close").invoke(lexerMock);
```

But since `verify()` requires a method on the mock type, the best way is to cast to the actual class or interface with `close()`.  
If you cannot cast, use `Mockito.verify(lexerMock, times(1)).close()` only if `lexerMock` type has `close()` method visible at compile time.

